About
The UAE’s latest cultural landmark, Dubai Frame is an iconic structure that ‘frames’ impressive views of Old and New Dubai, while serving as a metaphorical bridge connecting the emirate’s rich past with its magnificent present. Dubai Frame celebrates the story of Dubai from its early establishment to its ambitious plans for future development. Launched in January 2018, the project comprises a 150-metre-high, 95-meter-wide structure being built to resemble a huge picture frame, through which landmarks representing modern Dubai such as Emirates Towers and Burj Khalifa can be seen on one side, while from the other side, visitors can view older parts of the city such as Deira and Karama. Exterior design of Dubai Frame was inspired from the logo of EXPO2020 and it is world's largest picture frame by Guinness World Records. According to Dubai Frame general policy, guests are requested to wear respectful clothing: shoulders and knees to be covered.
Duration: 1-2 hours

    Patience is a virtue when you are visiting Dubai Frame during peak hours, it was indeed worth the wait. We are queueing for more than 40 minutes just to reach the top floor. I asked one of the staff regarding the best time to visit without that much queuing, he said from 9 to 10 AM and evening from 7 to 9 .   • Andy B
    13 contributions
    Far better than the Burj
    Whilst the Frame is not as high as the Burj Khalifa nor affords as good views, it is a fraction of the price and you will not have to wait so long to get in and it is not as overcrowded. We did have to wait in the queue for about 40 minutes before we walked through the UAE in the past mini history tour, but when you don't have a time slot booked I guess you Kind of have to expect this. Views were great from the top, transparent walkway was cool and it wasn't overcrowded. Unlike the Burj you can see outside from the lift as you ascend. The UAE future 360 show at the end was very cleverly done. Whole thing including queueing probably took about 2 hours. Very nice gardens etc outside. Easy to access off stop 15 on the Big Bus Tour.

Dear valued guest, Warm greetings from Dubai Frame and thank you for reaching out to us. Kindly be advised that if you miss your specific time slot, you still can use your ticket on the SAME DAY.
